<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/7633> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #7633" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. pl. 103. See MRR 1.563. Recorded in Auct. Vir. Ill. 73.1, as a Tr. pl., colleague of Saturninus, who attempted to veto his African land bill. See RE no. 17, and in MRR 2.537 read Tr. pl. (not mil.).\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3590> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3590" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Driven by violence from the Forum when he attempted to veto Saturninus' bill to assign land to Marius' veterans (Auct. Vir. Ill. 73.1)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/3589> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #3589" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Niccolini (FTP 194) suggests that he may be the M. Baebius who was murdered by Marius in 86 (App. BC 1.72; Flor. 2.9.14; Augustin. CD 3.27; cf. Lucan 2.119 and Schol. Bern.)." .
